Reference manual p 155:

    The syntax for the FindNewPath and FindPath procedures should
    read as follows:

        PROCEDURE FindNewPath(
                     name : ARRAY OF CHAR;
                     VAR fullname : ARRAY OF CHAR) : BOOLEAN;

        PROCEDURE FindPath(
                   name : ARRAY OF CHAR;
                   VAR fullname : ARRAY OF CHAR) : BOOLEAN;


    The description of these procedures omits the following information:

        FindNewPath always returns TRUE.

        FindPath returns TRUE if the requested file was found.

Reference manual p 157:

    The description of the Open procedure should read as follows:

        ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        Open               Open file for reading using redirection
        ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

                PROCEDURE Open( name : ARRAY OF CHAR ) : File;

        The Open procedure is used to open a file for reading. In
        this way it is identical to the OpenRead procedure in the
        FIO module. This version of Open, however, uses the
        redirection file to determine the full path string of the
        file. The FIO version of OpenRead only looks in the current
        directory.

Reference manual p 157:

    The OpenRW procedure is not documented in the manual. The syntax
    and description are as follows:

        ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        OpenRW                         Open file using redirection
        ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

                PROCEDURE OpenRW( name : ARRAY OF CHAR ) : File;

        The OpenRW procedure is used to open a file for processing.
        In this way it is identical to the Open procedure in the FIO
        module. This version of Open, however, uses the redirection
        file to determine the full path string of the file. The FIO
        version of Open only looks in the current directory.

